The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Day III Highlights
                                                                                                                                                                                                     Day III Highlights
                      
	 When he claimed the wicket of Tendulkar, Mendis claimed his 25th wicket of the series. He became the highest wickettaker in a three-Test series on debut.         
	 When on 32 Sehwag (1002) completed 1000 runs in the year 2008. He is only the second batsman to do so this year. The other batsman being South African Graeme Smith who has 1179 runs so far this year.         
	 It is the second time in his career that Sehwag has scored 1000 runs in a year. In 2004 he had scored 1147 runs.         
	 Muttiah Muralidharan has dismissed Sourav Ganguly 9 times in his career so far. It is the most number of times any bowler has dismissed the former India captain.         
	 The 80-run partnership between Kumar Sangakkara and Prasanna Jayawardene is now the highest for the 7th wicket on the P. Sara Stadium by Sri Lanka. The previous highest was 70 by Hashan Tillekeratne and Kumar Dharmasena vs New Zealand in 2003.         
	 When he claimed the wicket of Parthiv Patel, Muralidharan claimed his 50th wicket at the P. Sara stadium. It is the 4th Sri Lankan venue where he has claimed 50 wickets or more. The other venues being Colombo SSC (160), Kandy (117) and Galle (96).         
	 Shane Warne is the only other cricketer to claim 50 wickets on 4 different grounds. Warne achieved this feat at Brisbane (68), Sydney (64), Adelaide and Melbourne (56 each).               
